You are executing the 01-PRD-Generation skill. Your mandate is to produce a comprehensive Product Requirements Document that bridges strategic vision with detailed feature specifications per IEEE 29148 and IEEE 1233.

1. Read ../project_context/vision.md, ../project_context/features.md, and ../project_context/stakeholders.md. Optionally read ../output/Vision_Statement.md if it exists. Log all file paths. Halt if vision.md or features.md is missing.
2. Write Document Header with project name (from vision.md), version 1.0, current date, and document status "Draft".
3. Write Executive Summary: one paragraph in active voice stating what the product does, who it serves, and why it matters. No marketing language.
4. Write Market Context: extract problem space from the vision.md Problem Statement, identify target market segments from stakeholders.md, note competitive constraints from domain context. Flag inferences with [INFERRED].
5. Write Product Objectives: one objective per business goal from vision.md. Each shall follow SMART format with a quantitative metric and timeline. Flag unmeasurable goals with [METRIC-TBD].
6. Write Feature Priority Matrix as a markdown table. For each feature in features.md: assess Priority (Critical/High/Medium/Low) by business impact, Effort (S/M/L/XL) by technical complexity, Value (High/Medium/Low) by user benefit, MoSCoW (Must/Should/Could/Won't) by MVP criticality. Include a Rationale column with one-sentence justification.
7. Write Success Metrics: 3-5 KPIs, each with Baseline (current state), Target (desired state), Method (how measured), and Timeline. Flag unknown baselines with [BASELINE-TBD].
8. Write Constraints (budget, timeline, technology, regulatory from vision.md), Dependencies (external systems, APIs, third-party services), and Release Strategy (phased rollout mapping features to releases ordered by priority).
9. Write Standards Traceability appendix: a table mapping each PRD section to the corresponding IEEE 29148-2018 and IEEE 1233-1998 clause numbers. Write the completed document to ../output/PRD.md. Log section count and feature count.
